---
description: "Playwright E2E testing conventions for CachyOS/Arch"
globs:
  - "tests/**"
  - "**/*.spec.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Testing

- Playwright must launch **system-installed Chromium only** on this machine (CachyOS), not
  Playwright's own bundled downloads and not Firefox/WebKit — Arch is not an officially
  supported platform for `npx playwright install` and it reliably fails or produces
  broken binaries, and visual regression across browsers is out of scope. Configure
  `launchOptions.executablePath` pointing at `/usr/bin/chromium` (installed via
  `pacman`), verifying the actual path on this machine rather than assuming. **No
  Firefox, no WebKit, no `toHaveScreenshot()` in the main `test:e2e` script** — visual
  regression is a separate, opt-in script if ever added.
- Use Playwright's `webServer` config option to start `hugo server` against
  `exampleSite/` automatically around the test run, rather than manually backgrounding a
  dev server in Fish shell — this avoids Fish's job-control/`wait` semantics differing
  from bash-oriented CI scripts.
- One spec file per feature area under `tests/e2e/specs/`: `sidebar.spec.ts`,
  `toc.spec.ts`, `infobox.spec.ts`, `theme-toggle.spec.ts`, `search.spec.ts`. Don't
  combine unrelated feature assertions into one spec file.
- Every spec targets `exampleSite/` content — never test a template/shortcode against ad
  hoc inline HTML; the example site is the single source of truth for E2E fixtures.
